            <p>Dissolving a Pennsylvania LLC or corporation requires several steps: obtaining a vote of the members or shareholders to approve dissolution, winding up business affairs and paying all outstanding debts and obligations, filing a Certificate of Dissolution (for LLCs) or Articles of Dissolution (for corporations) with the Pennsylvania Department of State, filing final state and federal tax returns, and canceling any business licenses, permits, and registrations. An attorney ensures the dissolution is done properly so that you are not personally liable for any future obligations that surface after the business is closed.</p>
