            <h3>How do I add a beneficiary to my deed in Pennsylvania?</h3>
            <p>Adding a beneficiary to a deed — or more accurately, adding a person to the deed or creating a transfer-on-death designation — requires careful consideration. Simply adding a child's name to your deed creates an immediate ownership interest, which can trigger gift tax implications, expose the property to the new owner's creditors, and complicate a future sale. A better approach may be a transfer-on-death deed (if available), a revocable trust, or a life estate deed — each with different legal and tax consequences. Consult with an attorney before making any changes to your property title.</p>
