        <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>What is the Pennsylvania inheritance tax rate?</h3>
            <p>Pennsylvania imposes inheritance tax on assets passing at death at the following rates: 0% to a surviving spouse, 4.5% to lineal descendants (children, grandchildren) and lineal ancestors (parents), 12% to siblings, and 15% to all other heirs including nieces, nephews, and non-relatives. Certain assets are exempt, including life insurance proceeds, certain farmland, and small family-owned businesses meeting specific criteria. The tax is due within nine months of death, and a 5% discount is available if paid within three months. Our <a href="/resources/">Inheritance Tax Guide</a> provides a detailed breakdown.</p>
