        <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>How long does it take to settle an estate in Pennsylvania?</h3>
            <p>A straightforward estate in Pennsylvania typically takes nine to twelve months to settle. The timeline includes obtaining Short Certificates, notifying creditors and beneficiaries, gathering and valuing assets, filing the Pennsylvania inheritance tax return (due within nine months), obtaining tax clearances, and making final distributions. Estates involving real estate sales, disputed claims, tax audits, or litigation can take significantly longer. Under 20 Pa.C.S. § 3532, executors are expected to settle estates within a reasonable time but are generally protected from suit by beneficiaries during the first year after appointment.</p>
